A 32-year-old man, Ojo Matthew, has been arrested by the personnel of the Osun State Command of the Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), for allegedly stealing a motorcycle in Ede, Osun State. The Osun Commandant of the NSCDC, Emmanuel Ocheja, also announced that the culprit, Ojo, who is a native of Ede South Local Government Area, was caught in the act of stealing the motorcycle by vigilant residents who alerted the corps. Confirming the arrest, Daniel Adigun, the Public Relations Officer of the command, told DAILY POST that upon arrest, the suspect confessed that his plan was not to steal the motorcycle. Adigun stated that the suspect confessed that he planned to drain the fuel from the motorcycle so as to use it on his own before luck ran out on him. The Command spokesperson, who also stated that the NSCDC Commandant had given the command the authorisation to thoroughly investigate the case, added that it was prepared and committed to safeguarding the lives and property of citizens of Osun State. While warning miscreants to steer clear of the state as the corps, the command spokesperson made it known that none of them would escape the long arm of the law and they will be diligently prosecuted in accordance to the laws of the land.